00:06:26.140 --> 00:06:30.670 align:middle line:84%
>> My awakening to who I am
really occurred when I was

00:06:30.670 --> 00:06:32.980 align:middle line:84%
in high school and
entering college--

00:06:32.980 --> 00:06:36.490 align:middle line:84%
and was never really
successful in the classroom,

00:06:36.490 --> 00:06:39.860 align:middle line:84%
really had an
inability to focus.

00:06:39.860 --> 00:06:42.700 align:middle line:84%
And I was led to an organization
called the Mental Fitness

00:06:42.700 --> 00:06:46.810 align:middle line:84%
Company and became aware very
quickly of your father's work.

00:06:46.810 --> 00:06:51.880 align:middle line:84%
And that book, really, I
read about seven times.

00:06:51.880 --> 00:06:54.040 align:middle line:90%
Just read it, stopped.

00:06:54.040 --> 00:06:55.040 align:middle line:90%
Read it, stopped.

00:06:55.040 --> 00:06:55.840 align:middle line:90%
I was amazed.

00:06:55.840 --> 00:06:58.030 align:middle line:84%
It totally-- many
of the things were

00:06:58.030 --> 00:07:00.850 align:middle line:84%
said in that book that
were said in a way

00:07:00.850 --> 00:07:02.500 align:middle line:90%
that I could understand.

00:07:02.500 --> 00:07:05.320 align:middle line:84%
And it really led
me to continuing

00:07:05.320 --> 00:07:07.960 align:middle line:90%
my path of personal growth.

00:07:07.960 --> 00:07:09.280 align:middle line:90%
>> My name is Dina Buechler.

00:07:09.280 --> 00:07:11.060 align:middle line:90%
I live here in Austin.

00:07:11.060 --> 00:07:14.650 align:middle line:84%
And what I notice here
tonight is that I actually

00:07:14.650 --> 00:07:19.000 align:middle line:84%
have two of the people in
minority here with me tonight,

00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:21.580 align:middle line:90%
which would be teenagers.

00:07:21.580 --> 00:07:26.080 align:middle line:84%
And my concern, and
it is a concern,

00:07:26.080 --> 00:07:29.000 align:middle line:84%
is why aren't there
more teenagers here?

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:32.680 align:middle line:84%
Why aren't there more parents
with their teenagers here

00:07:32.680 --> 00:07:33.500 align:middle line:90%
tonight?

00:07:33.500 --> 00:07:36.580 align:middle line:84%
This place should
be overflowing.

00:07:36.580 --> 00:07:38.570 align:middle line:90%
That's my concern.

00:07:38.570 --> 00:07:41.200 align:middle line:84%
So I would like you
to address that.

00:07:41.200 --> 00:07:43.720 align:middle line:84%
>> My own enlightenment came
through a lot of adversity.

00:07:43.720 --> 00:07:45.370 align:middle line:84%
And you guys had
the good fortune

00:07:45.370 --> 00:07:49.970 align:middle line:84%
of having great parents to
really lead you and guide you.

00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:51.850 align:middle line:84%
But you were still
kids, and you were still

00:07:51.850 --> 00:07:53.060 align:middle line:90%
teenagers at one point.

00:07:53.060 --> 00:07:55.300 align:middle line:84%
So how did your
parents discipline you?

00:07:55.300 --> 00:07:57.050 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we're talking
about the teenagers.

00:07:57.050 --> 00:07:59.628 align:middle line:84%
And what's it like to get
in trouble by Dr. Chopra?

00:07:59.628 --> 00:08:01.580 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:08:01.580 --> 00:08:03.020 align:middle line:90%


00:08:03.020 --> 00:08:04.020 align:middle line:90%
I mean, what does he do?

00:08:04.020 --> 00:08:04.996 align:middle line:90%
Did you get sent to your room?

00:08:04.996 --> 00:08:06.913 align:middle line:84%
What kind of things did
he get mad at you for?

00:08:06.913 --> 00:08:09.577 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, just to answer
that question, my mom,

00:08:09.577 --> 00:08:11.910 align:middle line:84%
unfortunately, had to take
up the role of disciplinarian

00:08:11.910 --> 00:08:13.327 align:middle line:84%
because he wasn't
very good at it.

00:08:13.327 --> 00:08:17.160 align:middle line:10%
But I'm glad--

00:08:17.160 --> 00:08:19.410 align:middle line:10%
I think, and just
to touch briefly

00:08:19.410 --> 00:08:22.830 align:middle line:10%
on some of your questions
also, the relationship

00:08:22.830 --> 00:08:26.160 align:middle line:10%
I had with my parents
is that my parents were

00:08:26.160 --> 00:08:30.330 align:middle line:10%
able to step out of the role
of just being the authority

00:08:30.330 --> 00:08:31.410 align:middle line:10%
figure.

00:08:31.410 --> 00:08:34.409 align:middle line:84%
They were able to be my
friend, I always felt,

00:08:34.409 --> 00:08:37.950 align:middle line:84%
because they established
a relationship where

00:08:37.950 --> 00:08:40.110 align:middle line:84%
I could go to them
with anything,

00:08:40.110 --> 00:08:42.700 align:middle line:84%
and I felt
comfortable with that.

00:08:42.700 --> 00:08:45.990 align:middle line:84%
I screwed up, and
I got into trouble.

00:08:45.990 --> 00:08:47.340 align:middle line:90%
And I got punished for that.

00:08:47.340 --> 00:08:51.000 align:middle line:84%
And the form of punishment
was sometimes grounding.

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:58.690 align:middle line:84%
It was sometimes just being
screamed at, basically.

00:08:58.690 --> 00:09:00.870 align:middle line:84%
But there was also
always a release.

00:09:00.870 --> 00:09:03.210 align:middle line:84%
And there was an
ability by my parents

00:09:03.210 --> 00:09:07.230 align:middle line:84%
by leading by example to let
go, and to move on, and also

00:09:07.230 --> 00:09:09.630 align:middle line:84%
then step out of just
that authority role

00:09:09.630 --> 00:09:10.940 align:middle line:90%
and have fun together.

00:09:10.940 --> 00:09:13.652 align:middle line:84%
And that's one of the
things with my dad,

00:09:13.652 --> 00:09:15.360 align:middle line:84%
one of the best parts
of our relationship

00:09:15.360 --> 00:09:18.360 align:middle line:84%
is that we've had the ability to
just have a good time together,

00:09:18.360 --> 00:09:20.450 align:middle line:84%
and not worrying about
who is the parent, and who

00:09:20.450 --> 00:09:22.050 align:middle line:84%
is the child, who
was the student,

00:09:22.050 --> 00:09:23.050 align:middle line:90%
and who was the teacher.

00:09:23.050 --> 00:09:24.790 align:middle line:84%
We sort of interchange
those roles.

00:09:24.790 --> 00:09:27.240 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's the
most valuable thing

00:09:27.240 --> 00:09:29.820 align:middle line:90%
that I gained from my parents.

00:09:29.820 --> 00:09:33.580 align:middle line:84%
>> My parents didn't do the
thing that most parents do,

00:09:33.580 --> 00:09:36.990 align:middle line:84%
which is to call each other Mom
and Dad in my presence so that

00:09:36.990 --> 00:09:39.190 align:middle line:84%
I would do the
same as I grew up.

00:09:39.190 --> 00:09:41.190 align:middle line:10%
And so I call them John and Deo.

00:09:41.190 --> 00:09:43.823 align:middle line:10%
And the philosophy
behind that was

00:09:43.823 --> 00:09:45.240 align:middle line:10%
that they wanted
to be my parents,

00:09:45.240 --> 00:09:47.240 align:middle line:10%
but they wanted to be
much more than my parents.

00:09:47.240 --> 00:09:48.720 align:middle line:10%
They wanted to be my friends.

00:09:48.720 --> 00:09:51.420 align:middle line:84%
And they felt that if
we were to get stuck

00:09:51.420 --> 00:09:53.370 align:middle line:84%
in roles of
parent-child, then that

00:09:53.370 --> 00:09:58.170 align:middle line:84%
would limit our ability to grow
into new forms of relationship

00:09:58.170 --> 00:09:59.400 align:middle line:90%
as I got older.

00:09:59.400 --> 00:10:02.908 align:middle line:84%
And that's just
one symbolic thing.

00:10:02.908 --> 00:10:05.200 align:middle line:84%
I'm not saying that people
should or shouldn't do that.

00:10:05.200 --> 00:10:08.370 align:middle line:84%
But in my case, that was one
of the things that they did.

00:10:08.370 --> 00:10:10.590 align:middle line:84%
And another thing
is to explain why.

00:10:10.590 --> 00:10:12.970 align:middle line:84%
And to say "because
I told you so"

00:10:12.970 --> 00:10:15.990 align:middle line:84%
is one of the dumbest
responses I could ever

00:10:15.990 --> 00:10:19.110 align:middle line:84%
imagine to being asked, why
are you telling me to do this?

00:10:19.110 --> 00:10:22.320 align:middle line:84%
I think that kids always
have a right to know why.

00:10:22.320 --> 00:10:24.522 align:middle line:84%
And even then, to
have it be a command,

00:10:24.522 --> 00:10:25.980 align:middle line:84%
I think commands
should be reserved

00:10:25.980 --> 00:10:29.028 align:middle line:90%
for very urgent circumstances.

00:10:29.028 --> 00:10:30.820 align:middle line:84%
And the rest of the
time, there's requests.

00:10:30.820 --> 00:10:31.730 align:middle line:90%
There's suggestions.

00:10:31.730 --> 00:10:32.530 align:middle line:90%
There's guidance.

00:10:32.530 --> 00:10:33.360 align:middle line:90%
There's input.

00:10:33.360 --> 00:10:34.500 align:middle line:90%
There's ideas.

00:10:34.500 --> 00:10:36.450 align:middle line:84%
And if people are
always giving commands,

00:10:36.450 --> 00:10:38.070 align:middle line:84%
then the kid's not going
to respect it anymore

00:10:38.070 --> 00:10:39.653 align:middle line:84%
because they know
that not all of them

00:10:39.653 --> 00:10:42.130 align:middle line:84%
are that important, that you
must do it no matter what.

00:10:42.130 --> 00:10:44.080 align:middle line:84%
You know, yeah, there's life
and death situations where

00:10:44.080 --> 00:10:45.913 align:middle line:84%
a parent's got to give
a command on the spot

00:10:45.913 --> 00:10:48.430 align:middle line:84%
however forcefully it
takes to get the job done.

00:10:48.430 --> 00:10:51.360 align:middle line:84%
But there's a lot of situations
where it's like, put that down,

00:10:51.360 --> 00:10:55.140 align:middle line:84%
rather than explaining why, and
then assuming that the kid has

00:10:55.140 --> 00:10:57.540 align:middle line:84%
the brains to respond
appropriately, and make

00:10:57.540 --> 00:10:59.790 align:middle line:84%
their own sensible decision,
and learn from it if they

00:10:59.790 --> 00:11:01.110 align:middle line:90%
make a dumb decision.

00:11:01.110 --> 00:11:05.400 align:middle line:84%
And my parents really did that
with me all the way through.

00:11:05.400 --> 00:11:07.380 align:middle line:10%
So for example, with
sugar, rather than saying,

00:11:07.380 --> 00:11:10.230 align:middle line:10%
don't eat sugar, which they
felt sugar wouldn't be the best

00:11:10.230 --> 00:11:13.440 align:middle line:10%
thing for me, they explained
to me how sugar affects blood

00:11:13.440 --> 00:11:16.292 align:middle line:10%
sugar levels, and how people
feel tired after they eat it

00:11:16.292 --> 00:11:18.375 align:middle line:10%
a little while later as
their blood sugar goes up,

00:11:18.375 --> 00:11:19.340 align:middle line:10%
and then it goes down.

00:11:19.340 --> 00:11:21.840 align:middle line:84%
And they said, next time you're
at a birthday party, notice.

00:11:21.840 --> 00:11:23.350 align:middle line:90%
I was like four at the time.

00:11:23.350 --> 00:11:25.325 align:middle line:84%
So the next time I was
at a birthday party--

00:11:25.325 --> 00:11:27.145 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:11:27.145 --> 00:11:29.420 align:middle line:90%


00:11:29.420 --> 00:11:32.820 align:middle line:84%
So, and you'd be
amazed so often parents

00:11:32.820 --> 00:11:34.230 align:middle line:90%
talk baby talk to their kids.

00:11:34.230 --> 00:11:35.320 align:middle line:90%
And they're like, oh, how cute.

00:11:35.320 --> 00:11:35.790 align:middle line:90%
Do you want this?

00:11:35.790 --> 00:11:37.470 align:middle line:84%
And I used to get
really insulted

00:11:37.470 --> 00:11:39.150 align:middle line:84%
when people would do that to
me because my parents didn't

00:11:39.150 --> 00:11:39.690 align:middle line:90%
do that to me.

00:11:39.690 --> 00:11:42.390 align:middle line:84%
They'd talk to me straight like
I was a real human being, which

00:11:42.390 --> 00:11:43.690 align:middle line:90%
I figured I was.

00:11:43.690 --> 00:11:46.440 align:middle line:84%
And so I remember going
to a birthday party

00:11:46.440 --> 00:11:48.610 align:middle line:84%
and noticing how everyone
was having a great time.

00:11:48.610 --> 00:11:49.920 align:middle line:90%
And then the cake came out.

00:11:49.920 --> 00:11:51.060 align:middle line:90%
And everyone ate the cake.

00:11:51.060 --> 00:11:52.620 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, they
were getting in fights,

00:11:52.620 --> 00:11:54.120 align:middle line:84%
and they were crabby,
and everything

00:11:54.120 --> 00:11:55.770 align:middle line:90%
was like really obnoxious.

00:11:55.770 --> 00:11:57.897 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, wow,
isn't that interesting.

00:11:57.897 --> 00:11:59.730 align:middle line:84%
And I never would've
noticed that otherwise,

00:11:59.730 --> 00:12:02.147 align:middle line:84%
but they told me to take a
look and to see what I noticed.

00:12:02.147 --> 00:12:03.600 align:middle line:90%
And then I knew it for myself.

00:12:03.600 --> 00:12:06.150 align:middle line:84%
And then it wasn't like, I
will never eat sugar again.

00:12:06.150 --> 00:12:08.400 align:middle line:84%
But I was like, I'm conscious
of how sugar affects me,

00:12:08.400 --> 00:12:11.910 align:middle line:84%
and I can make my own
choices with awareness.

00:12:11.910 --> 00:12:15.660 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's the key is
to respect a young person's

00:12:15.660 --> 00:12:20.708 align:middle line:84%
integrity and intelligence
enough to tell them the truth.

