00:12:30.710 --> 00:12:32.960 align:middle line:10%
But why don't we take a
little time now for each of us

00:12:32.960 --> 00:12:36.090 align:middle line:10%
to share a little more about
ourselves, our message, what we

00:12:36.090 --> 00:12:37.340 align:middle line:10%
want to share with all of you.

00:12:37.340 --> 00:12:39.830 align:middle line:10%
And then we'll move into some
more interactive parts again

00:12:39.830 --> 00:12:42.710 align:middle line:10%
a little later and also respond
to some of the questions that

00:12:42.710 --> 00:12:45.140 align:middle line:10%
have been shared with us.

00:12:45.140 --> 00:12:48.553 align:middle line:10%
>> So I just want to tell
a few stories, actually,

00:12:48.553 --> 00:12:50.720 align:middle line:10%
instead of really going
into what I'm doing and what

00:12:50.720 --> 00:12:53.750 align:middle line:10%
I've done, just to tell
you a little bit why,

00:12:53.750 --> 00:12:56.920 align:middle line:10%
what brought me here,
and how I ended up here.

00:12:56.920 --> 00:13:00.290 align:middle line:10%
I'm going to start with
some common questions.

00:13:00.290 --> 00:13:02.930 align:middle line:84%
When I was young, people
would always ask me--

00:13:02.930 --> 00:13:05.330 align:middle line:84%
I remember getting lost
in a mall one time.

00:13:05.330 --> 00:13:10.010 align:middle line:84%
And while I was sort of sitting
with the person, the security

00:13:10.010 --> 00:13:14.230 align:middle line:84%
person, as my mom came to find
me, she started asking me,

00:13:14.230 --> 00:13:16.650 align:middle line:84%
she looked at me and
said, where are you from?

00:13:16.650 --> 00:13:20.540 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I'm from Lincoln,
which is where I grew up,

00:13:20.540 --> 00:13:22.950 align:middle line:90%
in a town outside of Boston.

00:13:22.950 --> 00:13:25.250 align:middle line:84%
And she kind of was a
little bit perplexed.

00:13:25.250 --> 00:13:27.250 align:middle line:90%
And I said, you know, I--

00:13:27.250 --> 00:13:29.960 align:middle line:84%
and I even at seven years
old, or how ever old I was,

00:13:29.960 --> 00:13:31.820 align:middle line:84%
I knew kind of what
she was getting

00:13:31.820 --> 00:13:34.740 align:middle line:84%
at because I had gotten
accustomed to this sort

00:13:34.740 --> 00:13:35.540 align:middle line:90%
of question.

00:13:35.540 --> 00:13:37.830 align:middle line:84%
So I said, my parents
are from India.

00:13:37.830 --> 00:13:38.630 align:middle line:90%
And I grew up--

00:13:38.630 --> 00:13:40.040 align:middle line:90%
I was born in Boston.

00:13:40.040 --> 00:13:41.030 align:middle line:90%
I've grown up here--

00:13:41.030 --> 00:13:41.830 align:middle line:90%
blah, blah.

00:13:41.830 --> 00:13:44.120 align:middle line:84%
But it's something that
always sort of stayed with me.

00:13:44.120 --> 00:13:47.150 align:middle line:84%
And my skin tone is
the type, as I learned

00:13:47.150 --> 00:13:49.370 align:middle line:84%
when I went to college
in New York City, that

00:13:49.370 --> 00:13:53.780 align:middle line:84%
can pass for Hispanic, or
Mediterranean, or South

00:13:53.780 --> 00:13:58.660 align:middle line:84%
Asian, which is a great
advantage in New York City too,

00:13:58.660 --> 00:14:02.530 align:middle line:84%
but except if you're trying
to get a taxi late at night.

00:14:02.530 --> 00:14:05.520 align:middle line:90%


00:14:05.520 --> 00:14:06.880 align:middle line:90%
Yes, yes.

00:14:06.880 --> 00:14:08.940 align:middle line:84%
So, but then I got
to New York City.

00:14:08.940 --> 00:14:11.310 align:middle line:84%
And I had gotten so
used to this question

00:14:11.310 --> 00:14:14.580 align:middle line:84%
that I started to ask
it of all my roommates

00:14:14.580 --> 00:14:16.120 align:middle line:90%
and things like that.

00:14:16.120 --> 00:14:19.560 align:middle line:84%
And one thing I noticed is my
first day I got to college--

00:14:19.560 --> 00:14:22.290 align:middle line:84%
and I had an
African-American roommate.

00:14:22.290 --> 00:14:25.950 align:middle line:84%
And we became
friends, best friends.

00:14:25.950 --> 00:14:30.520 align:middle line:84%
And I met my neighbor
who was an Islamic guy,

00:14:30.520 --> 00:14:32.380 align:middle line:84%
and I grew up with
this Hindu background,

00:14:32.380 --> 00:14:33.640 align:middle line:90%
but we sort of hit it off.

00:14:33.640 --> 00:14:36.630 align:middle line:84%
One of my best friends who had
come from high school with me

00:14:36.630 --> 00:14:40.320 align:middle line:84%
was this Catholic guy who came
from a completely different

00:14:40.320 --> 00:14:42.750 align:middle line:84%
world, but we
seemed to get along.

00:14:42.750 --> 00:14:45.660 align:middle line:84%
My girlfriend was a
Chinese-American girl.

00:14:45.660 --> 00:14:48.000 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
I started to notice

00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:49.992 align:middle line:90%
we do have something in common.

00:14:49.992 --> 00:14:51.950 align:middle line:84%
Everybody asked each
other, where are you from,

00:14:51.950 --> 00:14:55.230 align:middle line:84%
and sort of suspects that you're
not from someplace familiar.

00:14:55.230 --> 00:14:57.690 align:middle line:84%
But we started to
find stuff in common.

00:14:57.690 --> 00:15:00.750 align:middle line:84%
So that was the second
sort of note that I made.

00:15:00.750 --> 00:15:02.310 align:middle line:84%
And then I'm going
to jump ahead.

00:15:02.310 --> 00:15:06.510 align:middle line:84%
And recently, as part of the
organization for which I work--

00:15:06.510 --> 00:15:08.640 align:middle line:84%
it's called Channel
One, and we broadcast

00:15:08.640 --> 00:15:11.760 align:middle line:84%
educational programming in
schools across the country.

00:15:11.760 --> 00:15:15.240 align:middle line:84%
I had gone to do a report
on the hurricane that

00:15:15.240 --> 00:15:18.570 align:middle line:84%
was in North Carolina and wasn't
as bad as everyone expected,

00:15:18.570 --> 00:15:21.720 align:middle line:84%
to the dismay of many
news people down there.

00:15:21.720 --> 00:15:24.160 align:middle line:90%
But we were there.

00:15:24.160 --> 00:15:25.380 align:middle line:90%
And I went to this kid.

00:15:25.380 --> 00:15:28.530 align:middle line:84%
And we were profiling a kid
as the family was preparing

00:15:28.530 --> 00:15:30.840 align:middle line:84%
for this hurricane that was
supposed to be the worst

00:15:30.840 --> 00:15:33.010 align:middle line:84%
hurricane, three times
worse than Andrew,

00:15:33.010 --> 00:15:35.320 align:middle line:84%
and all these terrible
things were predicted.

00:15:35.320 --> 00:15:37.470 align:middle line:90%
And I started talking to him.

00:15:37.470 --> 00:15:40.110 align:middle line:84%
He went to the
local high school.

00:15:40.110 --> 00:15:42.630 align:middle line:84%
And he and his
family had decided

00:15:42.630 --> 00:15:44.292 align:middle line:84%
not to leave and
evacuate but just sort

00:15:44.292 --> 00:15:45.500 align:middle line:90%
of hunker down in their home.

00:15:45.500 --> 00:15:47.470 align:middle line:90%
They had boarded up everything.

00:15:47.470 --> 00:15:50.200 align:middle line:84%
And so I started talking
to his grandmother, who

00:15:50.200 --> 00:15:53.160 align:middle line:84%
was in the corner
and an older woman.

00:15:53.160 --> 00:15:55.380 align:middle line:90%
And I said, so, are you scared?

00:15:55.380 --> 00:15:57.638 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they're saying
terrible things about this.

00:15:57.638 --> 00:15:59.180 align:middle line:84%
And do you feel safe
for your family?

00:15:59.180 --> 00:16:01.740 align:middle line:84%
And she said to me,
she said, oh, you know,

00:16:01.740 --> 00:16:04.470 align:middle line:84%
we're OK because God
will take care of us.

00:16:04.470 --> 00:16:09.210 align:middle line:84%
And if God willing, we'll
come out of this OK.

00:16:09.210 --> 00:16:11.758 align:middle line:84%
And I thought to myself,
wow, that's a lot of faith

00:16:11.758 --> 00:16:13.800 align:middle line:84%
she has because, man, they
say this thing's three

00:16:13.800 --> 00:16:16.830 align:middle line:84%
times the size of Texas
and all these things.

00:16:16.830 --> 00:16:18.737 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, you know?

00:16:18.737 --> 00:16:20.070 align:middle line:90%
And then I went to her grandson.

00:16:20.070 --> 00:16:22.470 align:middle line:84%
And I said, so, your grandmother
says, you know, god willing,

00:16:22.470 --> 00:16:24.053 align:middle line:84%
you guys are going
to make it through.

00:16:24.053 --> 00:16:27.580 align:middle line:84%
And I said, so, do
you think that's true?

00:16:27.580 --> 00:16:29.830 align:middle line:84%
And he said to me, he said,
oh, that's my grandmother.

00:16:29.830 --> 00:16:31.872 align:middle line:84%
We just sort of let her
think whatever she wants.

00:16:31.872 --> 00:16:33.190 align:middle line:90%
But we'll be OK.

00:16:33.190 --> 00:16:34.860 align:middle line:84%
And I said, so,
are you Christian?

00:16:34.860 --> 00:16:36.943 align:middle line:84%
Because the grandmother
had made it quite apparent

00:16:36.943 --> 00:16:38.203 align:middle line:90%
she was Christian.

00:16:38.203 --> 00:16:39.120 align:middle line:90%
And he said, oh, yeah.

00:16:39.120 --> 00:16:40.290 align:middle line:90%
I'm Christian.

00:16:40.290 --> 00:16:43.020 align:middle line:84%
And I said, do you
believe in God and stuff?

00:16:43.020 --> 00:16:45.870 align:middle line:84%
He said, oh, yeah, but he
just doesn't waste his time

00:16:45.870 --> 00:16:47.460 align:middle line:90%
with hurricanes.

00:16:47.460 --> 00:16:50.570 align:middle line:90%
So that was interesting to me.

00:16:50.570 --> 00:16:54.720 align:middle line:10%
I was, where's the discrepancy
between what his grandmother

00:16:54.720 --> 00:16:56.390 align:middle line:10%
thinks and what he thinks?

00:16:56.390 --> 00:16:58.860 align:middle line:84%
And it reminded me of another
incident about a year ago,

00:16:58.860 --> 00:17:02.580 align:middle line:84%
that I went to St. Louis, and
I did this story on the pope.

00:17:02.580 --> 00:17:05.609 align:middle line:84%
And we were at the
Kiel Center, which

00:17:05.609 --> 00:17:08.220 align:middle line:84%
has about 20,000-- seats
about 20,000 people.

00:17:08.220 --> 00:17:11.010 align:middle line:10%
And they had got young
people for this youth rally.

00:17:11.010 --> 00:17:14.940 align:middle line:10%
And I went around, and I
started asking the kids,

00:17:14.940 --> 00:17:16.440 align:middle line:10%
are you guys Catholic?

00:17:16.440 --> 00:17:17.819 align:middle line:90%
And half of them said yes.

00:17:17.819 --> 00:17:18.947 align:middle line:90%
Half of them said no.

00:17:18.947 --> 00:17:21.030 align:middle line:84%
And then I asked the ones
who said yes, so I said,

00:17:21.030 --> 00:17:24.494 align:middle line:84%
do you follow the
rules, being Catholic?

00:17:24.494 --> 00:17:25.619 align:middle line:90%
And they said, oh, no, man.

00:17:25.619 --> 00:17:29.040 align:middle line:84%
That's too-- it's
too much for us.

00:17:29.040 --> 00:17:32.580 align:middle line:84%
They knew exactly
what I was getting at.

00:17:32.580 --> 00:17:36.300 align:middle line:10%
And I said, so, then
why are you here?

00:17:36.300 --> 00:17:37.942 align:middle line:84%
You guys, some of
you aren't Catholic.

00:17:37.942 --> 00:17:39.900 align:middle line:84%
Some of you don't believe
in some of the things

00:17:39.900 --> 00:17:40.900 align:middle line:90%
that Catholics practice.

00:17:40.900 --> 00:17:42.990 align:middle line:84%
They said, yeah, but
it's the pope, man.

00:17:42.990 --> 00:17:45.000 align:middle line:90%
You know, it's the pope.

00:17:45.000 --> 00:17:48.030 align:middle line:84%
And to me, again-- all of a
sudden, I said, you know what?

00:17:48.030 --> 00:17:50.040 align:middle line:84%
Young people, they might
not follow the rules,

00:17:50.040 --> 00:17:52.200 align:middle line:90%
but they want to feel connected.

00:17:52.200 --> 00:17:53.340 align:middle line:90%
They want to feel--

00:17:53.340 --> 00:17:57.600 align:middle line:84%
or they feel connected, and
they want to understand how,

00:17:57.600 --> 00:17:58.680 align:middle line:90%
how they're connected.

00:17:58.680 --> 00:18:00.870 align:middle line:90%
And the last story--

00:18:00.870 --> 00:18:03.580 align:middle line:90%
recently, I had gone to India.

00:18:03.580 --> 00:18:06.180 align:middle line:10%
And I was reporting
on a story in Kashmir,

00:18:06.180 --> 00:18:08.970 align:middle line:10%
where there's this 52-year
conflict between India

00:18:08.970 --> 00:18:12.090 align:middle line:10%
and Pakistan over
this beautiful region,

00:18:12.090 --> 00:18:16.110 align:middle line:10%
but this non-strategic
region, of the world.

00:18:16.110 --> 00:18:17.560 align:middle line:10%
And they're just
fighting over it.

00:18:17.560 --> 00:18:20.400 align:middle line:10%
So I had gone up, and
I'd gone out marching

00:18:20.400 --> 00:18:23.820 align:middle line:10%
with this anti-insurgent group
as they searched for militants

00:18:23.820 --> 00:18:25.020 align:middle line:10%
who are in the region.

00:18:25.020 --> 00:18:28.690 align:middle line:84%
And we went out with AK-47s
and rocket launchers.

00:18:28.690 --> 00:18:31.950 align:middle line:84%
And, I mean, it was
intense because these guys

00:18:31.950 --> 00:18:33.120 align:middle line:90%
are taught to kill.

00:18:33.120 --> 00:18:34.830 align:middle line:84%
And I couldn't argue
with them about,

00:18:34.830 --> 00:18:36.510 align:middle line:84%
ultimately, we're
all the same, and we

00:18:36.510 --> 00:18:39.210 align:middle line:84%
come from the same place,
and blah, blah, blah,

00:18:39.210 --> 00:18:44.610 align:middle line:84%
because they are trained
to shoot on command.

00:18:44.610 --> 00:18:47.040 align:middle line:10%
And the funny part
is that the stuff

00:18:47.040 --> 00:18:48.960 align:middle line:10%
about being all
philosophical, that we all

00:18:48.960 --> 00:18:51.690 align:middle line:10%
come from the same place,
was so true in this case

00:18:51.690 --> 00:18:54.870 align:middle line:10%
because, ethnically, the guys
that they were trained to kill

00:18:54.870 --> 00:18:56.320 align:middle line:10%
were the same.

00:18:56.320 --> 00:18:58.560 align:middle line:90%
They share the same biology.

00:18:58.560 --> 00:19:02.010 align:middle line:90%
They share the same ethnicity.

00:19:02.010 --> 00:19:03.510 align:middle line:10%
And then I crossed
over to Pakistan,

00:19:03.510 --> 00:19:06.260 align:middle line:10%
and I started talking to
these so-called militants

00:19:06.260 --> 00:19:07.370 align:middle line:10%
or terrorists.

00:19:07.370 --> 00:19:10.880 align:middle line:10%
And I met with one
guy in a strip mall

00:19:10.880 --> 00:19:13.640 align:middle line:10%
in Islamabad, of all
places, a strip mall,

00:19:13.640 --> 00:19:15.260 align:middle line:10%
and I started asking questions.

00:19:15.260 --> 00:19:17.090 align:middle line:84%
And we talked for
about half an hour.

00:19:17.090 --> 00:19:19.290 align:middle line:84%
And I learned he
was 25 years old.

00:19:19.290 --> 00:19:21.350 align:middle line:90%
He was a computer engineer.

00:19:21.350 --> 00:19:23.100 align:middle line:84%
And so I asked
him after a while,

00:19:23.100 --> 00:19:25.120 align:middle line:84%
I said, so we hear there
are these terrorists.

00:19:25.120 --> 00:19:25.450 align:middle line:90%
Where are they?

00:19:25.450 --> 00:19:26.600 align:middle line:90%
I've got to talk to them.

00:19:26.600 --> 00:19:29.550 align:middle line:84%
And he said, oh, I'm
one of those terrorists.

00:19:29.550 --> 00:19:32.420 align:middle line:84%
He said, I've been trained
recently in Afghanistan.

00:19:32.420 --> 00:19:35.600 align:middle line:84%
And he listed all he
could use, grenades

00:19:35.600 --> 00:19:39.110 align:middle line:84%
and all these terrible
weapons he listed to me.

00:19:39.110 --> 00:19:41.062 align:middle line:90%
And I was sort of shocked.

00:19:41.062 --> 00:19:43.520 align:middle line:84%
And I said, so, after about
half an hour of talking to him,

00:19:43.520 --> 00:19:44.320 align:middle line:90%
I said, so, look.

00:19:44.320 --> 00:19:46.910 align:middle line:84%
I said, you're
Islamic or Muslim.

00:19:46.910 --> 00:19:49.700 align:middle line:84%
And I'm Hindu, or
I grew up Hindu.

00:19:49.700 --> 00:19:50.540 align:middle line:90%
And here we are.

00:19:50.540 --> 00:19:51.740 align:middle line:90%
And we're 25 years old.

00:19:51.740 --> 00:19:53.870 align:middle line:84%
And we seem to be
hitting it off.

00:19:53.870 --> 00:19:55.133 align:middle line:90%
We could be good friends.

00:19:55.133 --> 00:19:56.300 align:middle line:90%
And he thought for a moment.

00:19:56.300 --> 00:19:59.420 align:middle line:84%
And he said to me, he
said, you know what?

00:19:59.420 --> 00:20:00.770 align:middle line:90%
We could be good friends.

00:20:00.770 --> 00:20:04.370 align:middle line:84%
But as soon as I
cross the line--

00:20:04.370 --> 00:20:06.290 align:middle line:84%
and in this case, he
meant quite literally

00:20:06.290 --> 00:20:09.150 align:middle line:84%
when he crosses the border
as he's trained to do--

00:20:09.150 --> 00:20:13.730 align:middle line:84%
and he says, and my
commander tells me to kill,

00:20:13.730 --> 00:20:16.320 align:middle line:84%
he said, I would
look you in the eye,

00:20:16.320 --> 00:20:18.150 align:middle line:90%
and I would slit your throat.

00:20:18.150 --> 00:20:21.800 align:middle line:84%
And I wouldn't-- it wouldn't be
personal because, you're right.

00:20:21.800 --> 00:20:23.970 align:middle line:90%
We could be friends.

00:20:23.970 --> 00:20:27.260 align:middle line:84%
And I thought to
myself, I said, wow.

00:20:27.260 --> 00:20:28.790 align:middle line:90%
He meant the line literally.

00:20:28.790 --> 00:20:31.640 align:middle line:84%
But I thought to
myself, metaphorically,

00:20:31.640 --> 00:20:34.250 align:middle line:90%
or where is that line?

00:20:34.250 --> 00:20:36.482 align:middle line:84%
You can't even find it on
the ground, let alone--

00:20:36.482 --> 00:20:37.940 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you can
find it on the map.

00:20:37.940 --> 00:20:39.860 align:middle line:90%
But where is that line?

00:20:39.860 --> 00:20:44.020 align:middle line:84%
And I started to think
that line is internally.

00:20:44.020 --> 00:20:45.470 align:middle line:90%
It's somewhere in here.

00:20:45.470 --> 00:20:49.390 align:middle line:10%
And it's, unfortunately, it's
somewhere in here now too.

00:20:49.390 --> 00:20:50.190 align:middle line:90%
And I came back.

00:20:50.190 --> 00:20:52.015 align:middle line:84%
And this was just
a few months ago.

00:20:52.015 --> 00:20:53.390 align:middle line:84%
And I started to
think, you know,

00:20:53.390 --> 00:20:56.960 align:middle line:84%
I've got to start thinking
about how to talk about some

00:20:56.960 --> 00:20:58.460 align:middle line:90%
of these issues.

00:20:58.460 --> 00:21:02.480 align:middle line:10%
And I think in that
part of the world,

00:21:02.480 --> 00:21:04.610 align:middle line:10%
now they want the UN
to come in or the US

00:21:04.610 --> 00:21:06.080 align:middle line:10%
to come in and intervene.

00:21:06.080 --> 00:21:07.790 align:middle line:10%
And after hearing
that statement,

00:21:07.790 --> 00:21:11.090 align:middle line:10%
I knew that these United
Nations and task forces,

00:21:11.090 --> 00:21:14.270 align:middle line:10%
they can't come in and
resolve these sorts of things.

00:21:14.270 --> 00:21:17.420 align:middle line:84%
These guys, and I,
myself, have to go inward

00:21:17.420 --> 00:21:21.230 align:middle line:84%
and try to find the resolution
to conflicts like this.

00:21:21.230 --> 00:21:24.560 align:middle line:10%
And that's kind of what I've
dedicated in my work to.

00:21:24.560 --> 00:21:27.298 align:middle line:84%
And now, it's not all
such serious stuff.

00:21:27.298 --> 00:21:29.840 align:middle line:84%
I do a television program that's
geared towards young people.

00:21:29.840 --> 00:21:32.132 align:middle line:84%
And they don't want to just
hear about gruesome things,

00:21:32.132 --> 00:21:35.150 align:middle line:84%
like wars and AK-- they
liked the AK-47 part.

00:21:35.150 --> 00:21:40.580 align:middle line:90%
But so I write books.

00:21:40.580 --> 00:21:43.280 align:middle line:84%
And I do, recently, a
comic book because I

00:21:43.280 --> 00:21:45.030 align:middle line:90%
figured that was a cool place.

00:21:45.030 --> 00:21:47.150 align:middle line:84%
And we called it "The
Bulletproof Monk"

00:21:47.150 --> 00:21:49.500 align:middle line:84%
to sort of talk
about spirituality

00:21:49.500 --> 00:21:51.650 align:middle line:84%
but to talk about it
in a language that

00:21:51.650 --> 00:21:53.090 align:middle line:90%
applies to young people.

00:21:53.090 --> 00:21:56.340 align:middle line:84%
And as much as we want to
reach out to parents, for me,

00:21:56.340 --> 00:22:00.380 align:middle line:84%
it's about finding the language
that speaks to young people

00:22:00.380 --> 00:22:01.430 align:middle line:90%
directly.

00:22:01.430 --> 00:22:04.100 align:middle line:84%
And in many cases, they
want to hear things

00:22:04.100 --> 00:22:07.370 align:middle line:84%
that their parents might not
agree with because that's

00:22:07.370 --> 00:22:09.140 align:middle line:90%
really what they connect with.

00:22:09.140 --> 00:22:11.870 align:middle line:84%
And I think what
my mission really

00:22:11.870 --> 00:22:14.060 align:middle line:84%
has become is to be a
part of that movement,

00:22:14.060 --> 00:22:17.300 align:middle line:84%
to create that space, first
of all, where young people can

00:22:17.300 --> 00:22:21.500 align:middle line:84%
start to articulate themselves
and say-- sometimes when you

00:22:21.500 --> 00:22:24.650 align:middle line:84%
ask them and you engage them
about spirituality and things

00:22:24.650 --> 00:22:27.920 align:middle line:84%
like that, they say some
crazy, crazy things.

00:22:27.920 --> 00:22:31.220 align:middle line:84%
But I think giving
them the opportunity

00:22:31.220 --> 00:22:34.707 align:middle line:84%
to start voicing some of their
concerns and their priorities,

00:22:34.707 --> 00:22:36.290 align:middle line:84%
and what's important
to them, and what

00:22:36.290 --> 00:22:40.130 align:middle line:84%
are the things that they believe
in, whether or not the pope,

00:22:40.130 --> 00:22:41.450 align:middle line:90%
is very important.

00:22:41.450 --> 00:22:43.640 align:middle line:84%
And that's sort of
what's brought me here

00:22:43.640 --> 00:22:46.888 align:middle line:90%
and to talk to you guys.

00:22:46.888 --> 00:22:49.333 align:middle line:90%
