00:22:58.140 --> 00:23:00.720 align:middle line:84%
>> I want to tell a
few stories as well.

00:23:00.720 --> 00:23:01.590 align:middle line:90%
Let's see.

00:23:01.590 --> 00:23:03.930 align:middle line:10%
One defining moment
in my life occurred

00:23:03.930 --> 00:23:06.180 align:middle line:10%
when I was six years old.

00:23:06.180 --> 00:23:09.360 align:middle line:10%
And my dad and I
were going for a walk

00:23:09.360 --> 00:23:13.620 align:middle line:10%
at the beach in Victoria,
British Columbia, Canada,

00:23:13.620 --> 00:23:15.750 align:middle line:10%
where we were
living at that time.

00:23:15.750 --> 00:23:18.690 align:middle line:90%
And it was kind of a cold day.

00:23:18.690 --> 00:23:21.240 align:middle line:84%
And I remember walking along
and then, about 50 feet ahead

00:23:21.240 --> 00:23:26.190 align:middle line:84%
of us, seeing this mother
with her maybe 3-year-old son.

00:23:26.190 --> 00:23:29.100 align:middle line:84%
And she was screaming
at him and slapping him.

00:23:29.100 --> 00:23:31.650 align:middle line:90%
And he was screaming and crying.

00:23:31.650 --> 00:23:34.230 align:middle line:84%
And I heard her saying, don't
you ever talk back to me again.

00:23:34.230 --> 00:23:39.090 align:middle line:84%
And it looked like kind
of a violent situation.

00:23:39.090 --> 00:23:43.350 align:middle line:84%
And I reached over and
grabbed my dad's hand,

00:23:43.350 --> 00:23:45.960 align:middle line:90%
and he held my hand firmly.

00:23:45.960 --> 00:23:47.472 align:middle line:84%
And he kept on
walking towards them.

00:23:47.472 --> 00:23:49.680 align:middle line:84%
And then he said something
that I'll always remember.

00:23:49.680 --> 00:23:52.720 align:middle line:84%
He said, there's no
monsters in this world.

00:23:52.720 --> 00:23:54.270 align:middle line:84%
There's just people
who've been hurt.

00:23:54.270 --> 00:23:56.820 align:middle line:84%
And whenever you see someone
hurting somebody else,

00:23:56.820 --> 00:23:58.920 align:middle line:84%
it's because somebody
hurt them once.

00:23:58.920 --> 00:24:01.390 align:middle line:90%
You can know that for a fact.

00:24:01.390 --> 00:24:04.150 align:middle line:84%
And so the cycle of pain
just keeps on going.

00:24:04.150 --> 00:24:04.950 align:middle line:90%
People get hurt.

00:24:04.950 --> 00:24:05.950 align:middle line:90%
They lash out at others.

00:24:05.950 --> 00:24:09.790 align:middle line:84%
The cycle continues until
somebody says, enough.

00:24:09.790 --> 00:24:12.210 align:middle line:84%
And he said, well,
this is enough.

00:24:12.210 --> 00:24:15.050 align:middle line:84%
And he walked over
towards this woman.

00:24:15.050 --> 00:24:19.850 align:middle line:84%
And I was holding his
hand a little bit behind.

00:24:19.850 --> 00:24:21.750 align:middle line:84%
And she was continuing
to yell at the child

00:24:21.750 --> 00:24:23.610 align:middle line:90%
and slap him in the face.

00:24:23.610 --> 00:24:25.830 align:middle line:84%
And he was screaming and
clearly very frightened.

00:24:25.830 --> 00:24:29.130 align:middle line:84%
And I could see
tears in his eyes.

00:24:29.130 --> 00:24:32.850 align:middle line:84%
And so they were so
caught up in their thing,

00:24:32.850 --> 00:24:35.670 align:middle line:84%
they didn't notice us
until we were right there.

00:24:35.670 --> 00:24:37.420 align:middle line:90%
And then my dad said, excuse me.

00:24:37.420 --> 00:24:42.310 align:middle line:84%
And she spun around and
looked pretty upset.

00:24:42.310 --> 00:24:48.380 align:middle line:84%
And then he said, it looked like
you were having a hard time,

00:24:48.380 --> 00:24:50.840 align:middle line:84%
and I wondered if we
could be of any help.

00:24:50.840 --> 00:24:53.930 align:middle line:84%
And she said, it's
none of your business,

00:24:53.930 --> 00:24:57.040 align:middle line:90%
and looked quite upset at him.

00:24:57.040 --> 00:24:59.100 align:middle line:84%
And he just said, well,
I'm sorry to bother you,

00:24:59.100 --> 00:25:02.730 align:middle line:84%
but I just wanted you to know
that we're here to support you

00:25:02.730 --> 00:25:03.930 align:middle line:90%
if there's any way we can.

00:25:03.930 --> 00:25:07.370 align:middle line:84%
And it looks like you're having
a bit of a rough time here.

00:25:07.370 --> 00:25:10.225 align:middle line:90%
And she stopped for a moment.

00:25:10.225 --> 00:25:12.350 align:middle line:84%
And I thought she might be
about to lash out again.

00:25:12.350 --> 00:25:15.470 align:middle line:84%
But then I saw this look of kind
of shame pass over her face.

00:25:15.470 --> 00:25:17.630 align:middle line:90%
And she said, I'm sorry.

00:25:17.630 --> 00:25:19.100 align:middle line:90%
I'm not normally like this.

00:25:19.100 --> 00:25:25.550 align:middle line:84%
It's just that I just broke
up with my boyfriend, his dad.

00:25:25.550 --> 00:25:27.050 align:middle line:84%
And it just seems
like everything's

00:25:27.050 --> 00:25:29.270 align:middle line:90%
falling apart around me.

00:25:29.270 --> 00:25:33.130 align:middle line:84%
And so then my dad
and her started

00:25:33.130 --> 00:25:34.270 align:middle line:90%
conversing a little bit.

00:25:34.270 --> 00:25:38.110 align:middle line:84%
And I pulled out this little
toy car I had in my pocket

00:25:38.110 --> 00:25:41.110 align:middle line:84%
and started playing with this
boy, whose name was Michael.

00:25:41.110 --> 00:25:43.390 align:middle line:84%
And we start playing on the
beach for a few minutes.

00:25:43.390 --> 00:25:45.885 align:middle line:84%
And I could see them
talking a little ways away.

00:25:45.885 --> 00:25:48.010 align:middle line:84%
Then at a certain point,
they came over towards us.

00:25:48.010 --> 00:25:50.830 align:middle line:84%
And I could see her
expressing her appreciation.

00:25:50.830 --> 00:25:53.710 align:middle line:84%
And then she said, it's
so good to have someone

00:25:53.710 --> 00:25:55.570 align:middle line:90%
to talk to about all this.

00:25:55.570 --> 00:25:58.660 align:middle line:84%
And then she came over, and
she picked him up and said,

00:25:58.660 --> 00:25:59.610 align:middle line:90%
it's OK now.

00:25:59.610 --> 00:26:00.610 align:middle line:90%
You don't have to worry.

00:26:00.610 --> 00:26:04.247 align:middle line:84%
We're in this together, and
we'll get through it together.

00:26:04.247 --> 00:26:05.080 align:middle line:90%
And I looked at him.

00:26:05.080 --> 00:26:06.940 align:middle line:84%
And I could see that he didn't
know whether to believe her

00:26:06.940 --> 00:26:08.030 align:middle line:90%
or not.

00:26:08.030 --> 00:26:10.560 align:middle line:84%
And he was still
kind of frightened.

00:26:10.560 --> 00:26:11.950 align:middle line:90%
And I handed him the toy car.

00:26:11.950 --> 00:26:14.020 align:middle line:90%
And I said, this is for you.

00:26:14.020 --> 00:26:17.962 align:middle line:84%
And this big smile
came over his face.

00:26:17.962 --> 00:26:19.420 align:middle line:84%
And then she said,
what do you say?

00:26:19.420 --> 00:26:21.420 align:middle line:84%
And she was kind of more
commanding than asking.

00:26:21.420 --> 00:26:25.682 align:middle line:84%
But he said, thank you, and
the smile got even bigger.

00:26:25.682 --> 00:26:26.890 align:middle line:90%
And then she said, thank you.

00:26:26.890 --> 00:26:29.770 align:middle line:84%
And then she carried him
off, and my dad picked me up

00:26:29.770 --> 00:26:31.240 align:middle line:90%
and carried me off.

00:26:31.240 --> 00:26:34.000 align:middle line:84%
And I never forgot
that moment because I'd

00:26:34.000 --> 00:26:36.542 align:middle line:84%
learned at the age of six,
not just through words

00:26:36.542 --> 00:26:38.500 align:middle line:84%
but through example,
about the power of meeting

00:26:38.500 --> 00:26:42.320 align:middle line:84%
hatred with love, which is
really what that was all about.

00:26:42.320 --> 00:26:44.860 align:middle line:84%
And it might seem like not
that significant an event.

00:26:44.860 --> 00:26:47.560 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure we've all seen things
like that happen before.

00:26:47.560 --> 00:26:51.100 align:middle line:84%
But so often, we turn
away, or we judge somebody

00:26:51.100 --> 00:26:53.350 align:middle line:84%
without really understanding
what's happening for them

00:26:53.350 --> 00:26:55.760 align:middle line:84%
or reaching out to make a
difference in their lives.

00:26:55.760 --> 00:26:59.800 align:middle line:84%
And I remember when
I was 10 years old,

00:26:59.800 --> 00:27:05.590 align:middle line:84%
to jump to another story, we had
a fruit fly problem, a big one,

00:27:05.590 --> 00:27:08.260 align:middle line:84%
like there were fruit flies
all over the house, clouds

00:27:08.260 --> 00:27:09.070 align:middle line:90%
and swarms.

00:27:09.070 --> 00:27:10.660 align:middle line:84%
And it was getting
kind of serious.

00:27:10.660 --> 00:27:12.202 align:middle line:10%
And at that time,
my dad was actually

00:27:12.202 --> 00:27:13.630 align:middle line:10%
writing "Diet For
a New America."

00:27:13.630 --> 00:27:16.460 align:middle line:10%
And he was writing the
chapter, the first chapter,

00:27:16.460 --> 00:27:18.460 align:middle line:10%
which deals with animals
and how they're really

00:27:18.460 --> 00:27:20.955 align:middle line:10%
very intelligent,
and in their own way,

00:27:20.955 --> 00:27:22.330 align:middle line:10%
and they certainly
have feelings.

00:27:22.330 --> 00:27:25.150 align:middle line:10%
And so we didn't know
what to do because here he

00:27:25.150 --> 00:27:26.860 align:middle line:10%
was writing this
amazing material

00:27:26.860 --> 00:27:28.190 align:middle line:10%
about the power of animals.

00:27:28.190 --> 00:27:30.380 align:middle line:10%
And yet it was a problem.

00:27:30.380 --> 00:27:32.420 align:middle line:84%
And my mom said, I
can't take it anymore.

00:27:32.420 --> 00:27:33.730 align:middle line:90%
I'm getting a fly swatter.

00:27:33.730 --> 00:27:35.438 align:middle line:84%
And I said, wait,
wait, wait, wait, wait.

00:27:35.438 --> 00:27:36.710 align:middle line:90%
Deo, stop.

00:27:36.710 --> 00:27:40.440 align:middle line:84%
Give me 24 hours to
use non-violent means.

00:27:40.440 --> 00:27:41.320 align:middle line:90%
She said, all right.

00:27:41.320 --> 00:27:43.270 align:middle line:90%
I'll give you one day.

00:27:43.270 --> 00:27:47.080 align:middle line:84%
But this has got to-- this
is pretty serious here.

00:27:47.080 --> 00:27:48.160 align:middle line:90%
So I wrote a letter.

00:27:48.160 --> 00:27:49.365 align:middle line:90%
I said, Dear fruit flies--

00:27:49.365 --> 00:27:52.330 align:middle line:90%


00:27:52.330 --> 00:27:56.530 align:middle line:84%
Let me first begin by
expressing my sincere respect.

00:27:56.530 --> 00:27:59.830 align:middle line:84%
I wish you the juiciest cow dung
piles and the biggest compost

00:27:59.830 --> 00:28:04.510 align:middle line:84%
heap for you and all
the generations to come.

00:28:04.510 --> 00:28:07.270 align:middle line:84%
Let me also state, however,
that this is our house

00:28:07.270 --> 00:28:08.470 align:middle line:90%
and not yours.

00:28:08.470 --> 00:28:10.060 align:middle line:90%
We pay rent here.

00:28:10.060 --> 00:28:11.290 align:middle line:90%
You don't.

00:28:11.290 --> 00:28:13.060 align:middle line:90%
We buy the food here.

00:28:13.060 --> 00:28:14.200 align:middle line:90%
You don't.

00:28:14.200 --> 00:28:17.140 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of food outside
that you can eat that we can't.

00:28:17.140 --> 00:28:19.190 align:middle line:84%
But our stomachs
are very limited.

00:28:19.190 --> 00:28:20.860 align:middle line:84%
So we can only eat
what's in here.

00:28:20.860 --> 00:28:23.200 align:middle line:84%
If you would simply go to
the compost pile outside,

00:28:23.200 --> 00:28:26.650 align:middle line:84%
there would be
enough for all of us.

00:28:26.650 --> 00:28:29.860 align:middle line:84%
Your presence here is creating
some real problems for us,

00:28:29.860 --> 00:28:32.090 align:middle line:84%
and we can't have
you here anymore.

00:28:32.090 --> 00:28:36.070 align:middle line:84%
So we want you to know that we
have purchased a fly swatter,

00:28:36.070 --> 00:28:39.835 align:middle line:84%
and we intend to use it if you
are not gone by dawn tomorrow.

00:28:39.835 --> 00:28:43.930 align:middle line:90%


00:28:43.930 --> 00:28:46.988 align:middle line:84%
So I then opened
a window partway.

00:28:46.988 --> 00:28:48.530 align:middle line:84%
We had tried opening
all the windows.

00:28:48.530 --> 00:28:50.580 align:middle line:84%
It seemed like more
flies came in before.

00:28:50.580 --> 00:28:52.960 align:middle line:84%
But at this point, I
opened a window partway.

00:28:52.960 --> 00:28:54.810 align:middle line:84%
And I put the note
up near the window

00:28:54.810 --> 00:28:56.560 align:middle line:84%
and drew an arrow
pointing to the opening,

00:28:56.560 --> 00:29:00.340 align:middle line:84%
and said, please exit
through this opening.

00:29:00.340 --> 00:29:03.010 align:middle line:84%
And then I read it aloud just
in case some of the fruit flies

00:29:03.010 --> 00:29:03.810 align:middle line:90%
couldn't read.

00:29:03.810 --> 00:29:06.720 align:middle line:90%


00:29:06.720 --> 00:29:10.690 align:middle line:84%
And they were buzzing all
over the place that day.

00:29:10.690 --> 00:29:12.900 align:middle line:84%
I went to sleep that night,
woke up in the morning.

00:29:12.900 --> 00:29:17.196 align:middle line:84%
There was not a
fly in the house.

00:29:17.196 --> 00:29:21.120 align:middle line:84%
I left the note up for a
couple weeks, took it down,

00:29:21.120 --> 00:29:22.980 align:middle line:90%
fruit flies coming back--

00:29:22.980 --> 00:29:26.795 align:middle line:84%
put it up, next
day at dawn, gone.

00:29:26.795 --> 00:29:28.650 align:middle line:84%
It tried it with
a raccoon that was

00:29:28.650 --> 00:29:30.900 align:middle line:84%
breaking into where
we fed our cats

00:29:30.900 --> 00:29:32.280 align:middle line:90%
and eating their cat food--

00:29:32.280 --> 00:29:33.855 align:middle line:90%
same thing, stopped coming.

00:29:33.855 --> 00:29:35.850 align:middle line:84%
I tried it with wasps
on a camping trip.

00:29:35.850 --> 00:29:37.295 align:middle line:90%
It didn't work.

00:29:37.295 --> 00:29:39.235 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:29:39.235 --> 00:29:42.630 align:middle line:90%


00:29:42.630 --> 00:29:46.030 align:middle line:84%
So two for three, I decided
I'd just leave it there

00:29:46.030 --> 00:29:46.830 align:middle line:90%
for the moment.

00:29:46.830 --> 00:29:48.930 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going into the
pest extermination business

00:29:48.930 --> 00:29:50.280 align:middle line:90%
quite yet.

00:29:50.280 --> 00:29:53.540 align:middle line:84%
But it was very inspirational
to me to see all that happen.

00:29:53.540 --> 00:29:57.050 align:middle line:84%
Now, am I presuming that
the flies read the letter?

00:29:57.050 --> 00:29:58.530 align:middle line:84%
Am I presuming that
they understood

00:29:58.530 --> 00:29:59.447 align:middle line:90%
my reading the letter?

00:29:59.447 --> 00:30:03.120 align:middle line:84%
Not necessarily, but there was
some level of communication

00:30:03.120 --> 00:30:04.680 align:middle line:90%
that obviously occurred.

00:30:04.680 --> 00:30:08.310 align:middle line:84%
And I grew up
believing in miracles.

00:30:08.310 --> 00:30:11.250 align:middle line:84%
I grew up believing that those
kind of things could happen.

00:30:11.250 --> 00:30:14.220 align:middle line:84%
And my mom and dad, even though
they were perhaps a little bit

00:30:14.220 --> 00:30:18.053 align:middle line:84%
skeptical, were willing
to give it a try.

00:30:18.053 --> 00:30:19.470 align:middle line:84%
One of the things
that I have seen

00:30:19.470 --> 00:30:21.895 align:middle line:84%
is a lot of adults have this
image that young people today

00:30:21.895 --> 00:30:22.695 align:middle line:90%
don't care.

00:30:22.695 --> 00:30:24.278 align:middle line:10%
And they say, oh,
it's so great to see

00:30:24.278 --> 00:30:27.330 align:middle line:10%
a young person who cares about
what's happening in the world.

00:30:27.330 --> 00:30:29.280 align:middle line:10%
And I get kind of
upset when I hear that.

00:30:29.280 --> 00:30:32.440 align:middle line:10%
Because the truth is that
young people today care a lot.

00:30:32.440 --> 00:30:34.380 align:middle line:84%
And they're tremendously
informed about what's

00:30:34.380 --> 00:30:35.920 align:middle line:90%
going on in the world.

00:30:35.920 --> 00:30:38.850 align:middle line:84%
And that's why they're so
cynical because they also

00:30:38.850 --> 00:30:41.868 align:middle line:84%
don't couple that
information with action.

00:30:41.868 --> 00:30:44.160 align:middle line:84%
And I think that whenever we
learn about something that

00:30:44.160 --> 00:30:47.085 align:middle line:84%
brings pain to us, we have to
have some way of responding,

00:30:47.085 --> 00:30:49.110 align:middle line:84%
of knowing that
our lives matter.

00:30:49.110 --> 00:30:50.990 align:middle line:84%
Because we have an
impulse to respond.

00:30:50.990 --> 00:30:52.770 align:middle line:84%
And when you see a
story on the television

00:30:52.770 --> 00:30:55.260 align:middle line:84%
about some vast disaster
or some horrible suffering,

00:30:55.260 --> 00:30:57.720 align:middle line:84%
you are powerless
to interact with it.

00:30:57.720 --> 00:31:00.343 align:middle line:84%
And it used to be that when
we'd learn about something,

00:31:00.343 --> 00:31:02.260 align:middle line:84%
it was usually around
us, and we could usually

00:31:02.260 --> 00:31:03.288 align:middle line:90%
do something about it.

00:31:03.288 --> 00:31:04.830 align:middle line:84%
But today, more and
more young people

00:31:04.830 --> 00:31:08.490 align:middle line:84%
are faced with this
feeling of powerlessness.

00:31:08.490 --> 00:31:10.320 align:middle line:84%
And when they feel
powerless, they

00:31:10.320 --> 00:31:15.120 align:middle line:84%
feel hopeless because power
and hope are very intertwined.

00:31:15.120 --> 00:31:18.430 align:middle line:84%
Well, I would say that we've
asked about several hundred

00:31:18.430 --> 00:31:21.030 align:middle line:84%
thousand students whether
they believe the world will

00:31:21.030 --> 00:31:23.490 align:middle line:84%
be a better place in 30 years,
with less violence and less

00:31:23.490 --> 00:31:24.290 align:middle line:90%
pollution.

00:31:24.290 --> 00:31:29.070 align:middle line:84%
And I'd say that 95% of
them do not, so that only 5%

00:31:29.070 --> 00:31:31.470 align:middle line:84%
of the high school students
in the United States today

00:31:31.470 --> 00:31:33.660 align:middle line:84%
are optimistic that
in one generation

00:31:33.660 --> 00:31:35.240 align:middle line:84%
the world will be
a better place.

00:31:35.240 --> 00:31:37.673 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's
pretty terrifying.

00:31:37.673 --> 00:31:39.090 align:middle line:84%
And no one can
hear that and think

00:31:39.090 --> 00:31:41.850 align:middle line:90%
that young people don't care.

00:31:41.850 --> 00:31:43.470 align:middle line:84%
The truth is that
youth care a lot.

00:31:43.470 --> 00:31:44.930 align:middle line:90%
They know a lot.

00:31:44.930 --> 00:31:49.390 align:middle line:84%
And it's up to adults to
try and set an example

00:31:49.390 --> 00:31:51.670 align:middle line:84%
that our lives do
make a difference.

00:31:51.670 --> 00:31:55.472 align:middle line:84%
And nothing is more powerful
than example on that.

00:31:55.472 --> 00:31:56.680 align:middle line:90%
I'll tell you something else.

00:31:56.680 --> 00:31:58.150 align:middle line:84%
Amongst the youth
who are active,

00:31:58.150 --> 00:31:59.860 align:middle line:84%
who are involved in
environmental clubs,

00:31:59.860 --> 00:32:02.350 align:middle line:84%
in social justice clubs,
in human rights clubs, who

00:32:02.350 --> 00:32:06.220 align:middle line:84%
are organizing for
positive change, 50% to 75%

00:32:06.220 --> 00:32:09.190 align:middle line:84%
believe the world will be a
better place in a generation.

00:32:09.190 --> 00:32:12.013 align:middle line:84%
Is that because they're more
informed or more educated?

00:32:12.013 --> 00:32:13.930 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps, but, ultimately,
it's because they're

00:32:13.930 --> 00:32:14.740 align:middle line:90%
doing something.

00:32:14.740 --> 00:32:16.930 align:middle line:84%
We tend to project
outward on the world

00:32:16.930 --> 00:32:21.053 align:middle line:84%
our expectations of the world
from what's inside of us.

00:32:21.053 --> 00:32:23.470 align:middle line:84%
I'm not saying you should
always go around with the belief

00:32:23.470 --> 00:32:25.570 align:middle line:90%
that things will get better.

00:32:25.570 --> 00:32:28.595 align:middle line:10%
My dad has often said that
hope is the belief that things

00:32:28.595 --> 00:32:30.220 align:middle line:10%
will get better, and
fear is the belief

00:32:30.220 --> 00:32:31.960 align:middle line:10%
that things will get worse.

00:32:31.960 --> 00:32:35.180 align:middle line:10%
And if we're really going to
have substance to our lives,

00:32:35.180 --> 00:32:38.810 align:middle line:10%
we need to draw our strength
not so much from hope or fear

00:32:38.810 --> 00:32:41.080 align:middle line:10%
as from love.

00:32:41.080 --> 00:32:42.070 align:middle line:90%
Because love matters.

00:32:42.070 --> 00:32:43.540 align:middle line:90%
Love is eternal.

00:32:43.540 --> 00:32:47.600 align:middle line:84%
Every bit of love we ever
express makes a difference.

00:32:47.600 --> 00:32:49.340 align:middle line:90%
It lasts forever.

00:32:49.340 --> 00:32:52.750 align:middle line:84%
So I think that, truly, we need
to know the power of our hearts

00:32:52.750 --> 00:32:55.240 align:middle line:84%
to make a difference in our
families, in our communities,

00:32:55.240 --> 00:32:56.632 align:middle line:90%
and in our world.

00:32:56.632 --> 00:32:58.090 align:middle line:84%
And if we can come
from that place,

00:32:58.090 --> 00:33:01.000 align:middle line:84%
we will see some, I think,
some awesome changes.

00:33:01.000 --> 00:33:05.650 align:middle line:84%
And I believe that we need to
find our strength not in what

00:33:05.650 --> 00:33:07.960 align:middle line:84%
we see in the world around
us but in the dreams that

00:33:07.960 --> 00:33:10.450 align:middle line:84%
live within us, in the
hopes, in the prayers,

00:33:10.450 --> 00:33:14.640 align:middle line:84%
in the possibilities that we
carry in our hearts and souls.

00:33:14.640 --> 00:33:18.750 align:middle line:84%
I believe that the problems
we face in the world today

00:33:18.750 --> 00:33:21.010 align:middle line:84%
are not more
reasons for despair.

00:33:21.010 --> 00:33:22.620 align:middle line:84%
They are a call to
a place inside us

00:33:22.620 --> 00:33:25.480 align:middle line:84%
that says, no,
this is not right.

00:33:25.480 --> 00:33:28.500 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to stand by and
let life on Earth be destroyed.

00:33:28.500 --> 00:33:31.470 align:middle line:84%
It's not OK with me that half
of the world's population

00:33:31.470 --> 00:33:34.620 align:middle line:84%
is malnourished or hungry,
the greatest percentage ever.

00:33:34.620 --> 00:33:37.410 align:middle line:84%
It's not OK with me that we
live under a nuclear shadow.

00:33:37.410 --> 00:33:39.990 align:middle line:84%
And all of human life,
all of life on this planet

00:33:39.990 --> 00:33:45.010 align:middle line:84%
could be annihilated
forever in an hour.

00:33:45.010 --> 00:33:47.950 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to stand
by and let this go on.

00:33:47.950 --> 00:33:49.880 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to do
something about it.

00:33:49.880 --> 00:33:56.020 align:middle line:84%
And we all carry inside of us,
I believe, anger, sorrow, grief,

00:33:56.020 --> 00:34:01.030 align:middle line:84%
and love in response to the
challenges of our times.

00:34:01.030 --> 00:34:04.010 align:middle line:84%
We need to be willing
to face those feelings.

00:34:04.010 --> 00:34:05.920 align:middle line:84%
But we can't just stop
with feeling them.

00:34:05.920 --> 00:34:08.750 align:middle line:84%
We can't just stop
with knowing the facts.

00:34:08.750 --> 00:34:11.620 align:middle line:84%
We've got to take the
next step into action.

00:34:11.620 --> 00:34:15.159 align:middle line:84%
What kind of action is as
diverse as the human race?

00:34:15.159 --> 00:34:17.679 align:middle line:84%
For me, it was starting an
organization, and doing a tour,

00:34:17.679 --> 00:34:20.980 align:middle line:84%
and putting on summer camps
to empower our generation

00:34:20.980 --> 00:34:22.000 align:middle line:90%
to make a difference.

00:34:22.000 --> 00:34:25.239 align:middle line:84%
For some people, it's
organizing recycling projects.

00:34:25.239 --> 00:34:28.270 align:middle line:84%
For some people, it's working
on environmental justice issues.

00:34:28.270 --> 00:34:31.030 align:middle line:84%
For some people, it's working
on the economic disparity

00:34:31.030 --> 00:34:32.620 align:middle line:90%
in our country and in our world.

00:34:32.620 --> 00:34:34.790 align:middle line:84%
For some people, it's
working to end homelessness.

00:34:34.790 --> 00:34:36.969 align:middle line:84%
There are so many areas
where we need to work.

00:34:36.969 --> 00:34:38.830 align:middle line:84%
We need to heal
racism, and sexism,

00:34:38.830 --> 00:34:40.210 align:middle line:90%
and the list goes on and on.

00:34:40.210 --> 00:34:41.043 align:middle line:90%
And you all know it.

00:34:41.043 --> 00:34:43.750 align:middle line:84%
And you could certainly
make a longer list than I.

00:34:43.750 --> 00:34:46.239 align:middle line:84%
And yet each of us, I
believe, inside of our hearts

00:34:46.239 --> 00:34:47.860 align:middle line:84%
carries a calling,
carries a dream,

00:34:47.860 --> 00:34:50.290 align:middle line:84%
carries a vision of what
this world could be,

00:34:50.290 --> 00:34:54.340 align:middle line:84%
and carries everything we
need to make the difference

00:34:54.340 --> 00:34:56.500 align:middle line:90%
that we're here for.

00:34:56.500 --> 00:34:59.610 align:middle line:84%
So what is that
difference, I ask, guests?

00:34:59.610 --> 00:35:01.900 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not saying that
we should all immediately

00:35:01.900 --> 00:35:02.710 align:middle line:90%
have our answer.

00:35:02.710 --> 00:35:05.080 align:middle line:84%
To me, it's a question
that I ask every day.

00:35:05.080 --> 00:35:09.040 align:middle line:84%
Saint Francis said, "Lord, make
me an instrument of peace."

00:35:09.040 --> 00:35:11.530 align:middle line:84%
So I ask myself
every day, how can I

00:35:11.530 --> 00:35:14.500 align:middle line:84%
be an instrument of peace and
healing in this world today

00:35:14.500 --> 00:35:17.410 align:middle line:84%
and in this moment,
and in this moment?

00:35:17.410 --> 00:35:19.710 align:middle line:84%
And I try to keep
coming back to that.

00:35:19.710 --> 00:35:21.640 align:middle line:84%
And I don't always
have the answer,

00:35:21.640 --> 00:35:24.340 align:middle line:84%
but I can always
return to the question.

00:35:24.340 --> 00:35:25.165 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:35:25.165 --> 00:35:27.640 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:35:27.640 --> 00:35:34.075 align:middle line:90%


00:35:34.075 --> 00:35:36.550 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:35:36.550 --> 00:35:39.050 align:middle line:10%


00:35:39.050 --> 00:35:46.280 align:middle line:10%
>> When I was growing up,
I, completely and totally,

00:35:46.280 --> 00:35:53.160 align:middle line:10%
dutifully rebelled against
everything that my parents

00:35:53.160 --> 00:35:53.960 align:middle line:10%
stand for.

00:35:53.960 --> 00:36:00.220 align:middle line:90%


00:36:00.220 --> 00:36:04.110 align:middle line:84%
When I was 17 years old, I
was sitting in juvenile hall.

00:36:04.110 --> 00:36:08.650 align:middle line:84%
I'd been there several
times that month.

00:36:08.650 --> 00:36:11.050 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:36:11.050 --> 00:36:18.270 align:middle line:90%


00:36:18.270 --> 00:36:25.530 align:middle line:84%
And the pain, the
internal stuff was so much

00:36:25.530 --> 00:36:31.280 align:middle line:84%
that when my father said, I
want you to try some meditation,

00:36:31.280 --> 00:36:37.550 align:middle line:84%
I was in enough pain to
hear him and say, oh, OK.

00:36:37.550 --> 00:36:39.950 align:middle line:84%
And also at that same time
was the first time in my life

00:36:39.950 --> 00:36:41.180 align:middle line:90%
where I was in trouble.

00:36:41.180 --> 00:36:44.190 align:middle line:84%
And I'd been in
trouble my whole life.

00:36:44.190 --> 00:36:48.020 align:middle line:84%
And it was always
everybody else.

00:36:48.020 --> 00:36:53.510 align:middle line:84%
Trouble was always about them,
and it was always external.

00:36:53.510 --> 00:36:55.850 align:middle line:84%
And for the first time I
saw like, oh, it's not.

00:36:55.850 --> 00:36:57.350 align:middle line:90%
It's internal.

00:36:57.350 --> 00:37:01.330 align:middle line:84%
The trouble is within
me, like Gotham

00:37:01.330 --> 00:37:04.660 align:middle line:84%
was saying, that line in
my heart, not a border,

00:37:04.660 --> 00:37:06.400 align:middle line:84%
but with that place
within me where

00:37:06.400 --> 00:37:12.370 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't showing up for myself.

00:37:12.370 --> 00:37:16.470 align:middle line:84%
And so although
I'd been brought up

00:37:16.470 --> 00:37:19.170 align:middle line:84%
with meditation, with
spiritual practice,

00:37:19.170 --> 00:37:22.950 align:middle line:84%
with compassion, with
love, unconditional love,

00:37:22.950 --> 00:37:24.090 align:middle line:90%
I didn't get it.

00:37:24.090 --> 00:37:25.380 align:middle line:90%
I didn't have it for myself.

00:37:25.380 --> 00:37:27.970 align:middle line:90%


00:37:27.970 --> 00:37:30.440 align:middle line:84%
And but in that moment,
for whatever reason,

00:37:30.440 --> 00:37:32.270 align:middle line:84%
even though it had been
said so many times,

00:37:32.270 --> 00:37:33.500 align:middle line:90%
you know, try meditation.

00:37:33.500 --> 00:37:34.820 align:middle line:90%
Try whatever.

00:37:34.820 --> 00:37:37.730 align:middle line:84%
My parents never tried
to push it on me at all.

00:37:37.730 --> 00:37:38.940 align:middle line:90%
But it was available.

00:37:38.940 --> 00:37:41.330 align:middle line:84%
The seeds had been
sown for sure.

00:37:41.330 --> 00:37:45.650 align:middle line:84%
And I started watching
my own inner experience.

00:37:45.650 --> 00:37:47.690 align:middle line:90%
I started looking at--

00:37:47.690 --> 00:37:50.310 align:middle line:84%
well, just watching my breath
was the first instruction

00:37:50.310 --> 00:37:51.110 align:middle line:90%
that I was given.

00:37:51.110 --> 00:37:52.640 align:middle line:90%
Just watch it.

00:37:52.640 --> 00:37:53.900 align:middle line:90%
Breathing in, count it.

00:37:53.900 --> 00:37:56.630 align:middle line:84%
Breath, say one,
breathing out, say two.

00:37:56.630 --> 00:37:57.980 align:middle line:90%
And so I sat there in my cell.

00:37:57.980 --> 00:37:59.930 align:middle line:90%
And I was like, 1, 2.

00:37:59.930 --> 00:38:02.610 align:middle line:90%


00:38:02.610 --> 00:38:04.073 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:38:04.073 --> 00:38:06.240 align:middle line:84%
And I was trying to get to
10, and I couldn't really

00:38:06.240 --> 00:38:09.020 align:middle line:90%
get to 10.

00:38:09.020 --> 00:38:11.290 align:middle line:84%
But eventually,
over the few months

00:38:11.290 --> 00:38:13.930 align:middle line:84%
that I was institutionalized,
and put into a group home,

00:38:13.930 --> 00:38:17.800 align:middle line:84%
and all that stuff that I went
through, I started to meditate.

00:38:17.800 --> 00:38:19.040 align:middle line:90%
And I also started to pray.

00:38:19.040 --> 00:38:26.990 align:middle line:84%
